SIMPLE: photochronograph
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Photochronograph
<hw>Pho`to*chron"o*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + <ets>chronograph</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An instrument for recording minute intervals
of time. The record is made by the power of a magnetic field, due to an
electric signaling current, to turn the plane of polarization of light.
A flash, coinciding in time and duration with the signal, is thus
produced and is photographed on a moving plate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>An instrument for the
photographic recording of star transits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photochronography</ent>⟦br⟧
